  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 13 high, 5 medium, 21 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Larnaca (LCA/LCLK); plus 10 other bases. 5 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, mist and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT). Network hotspots: Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Zaragoza (ZAZ/LEZG). Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and snow / blowing snow. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Glasgow (GLA/EGPF), Maastricht Aachen (MST/EHBK) and 9 others.",
